                                <p>
                                    <strong>Dusshera</strong>
                                </p>
                                <p align="justify">
                                    <img
                                        src="http://www.owcbangalore.org/images/dassera.jpg"
                                        width="120"
                                        height="120"
                                        hspace="5"
                                        align="right"
                                    />
                                    Celebrated all over India, only different
                                    in name, Dusshera remembers the victory of
                                    the goddess Durga over the demon Nowaddi.
                                    Each day of the festival is devoted to
                                    different goddesses, but the last days
                                    generally focus on Saraswati, goddess of
                                    learning. Craftsmen worship their tools;
                                    students worship their teachers, and
                                    musicians, their instruments.
                                    <br/>
                                    <em>All over India</em>
                                </p>
