                                    Christians all over India celebrate the
                                    birth of Christ, often marking their homes
                                    with a lit paper star. The holiday tends to
                                    be less commercialised in India than it
                                    does in Western countries. Many families
                                    share special Christmas sweets with one
                                    another, and all the ladies wear new saris
                                    in honor of the special day.
